name: Zeus
title: King of the Gods
description: Zeus is the king of the Olympian gods and the god of the sky, lightning, thunder, law, order, and justice.

name: Hera
title: Queen of the Gods
description: Hera is the queen of the Olympian gods and the goddess of marriage and family.

name: Athena
title: Goddess of Wisdom
description: Athena is the goddess of wisdom, strategic warfare, and the patron goddess of Athens.

name: Poseidon
title: God of the Sea
description: Poseidon is the god of the sea, earthquakes, and horses. He is one of the twelve Olympian gods.

name: Apollo
title: God of the Sun
description: Apollo is the god of the sun, music, poetry, and healing. He is also associated with prophecy.

name: Artemis
title: Goddess of the Hunt
description: Artemis is the goddess of the hunt, wilderness, and wild animals. She is the twin sister of Apollo.

name: Demeter
title: Goddess of Agriculture
description: Demeter is the goddess of agriculture, fertility, and the harvest. She is often associated with the growth of crops.

name: Hermes
title: Messenger of the Gods
description: Hermes is the messenger of the gods and the god of commerce, travel, and communication. He is also a guide to the Underworld.

name: Ares
title: God of War
description: Ares is the god of war, violence, and bloodshed. He represents the chaotic and brutal aspects of war.

name: Aphrodite
title: Goddess of Love and Beauty
description: Aphrodite is the goddess of love, beauty, and desire. She is often associated with the sea and emerged from the sea foam.

name: Dionysus
title: God of Wine
description: Dionysus is the god of wine, festivities, and ecstasy. He represents the joyous and liberating aspects of life.

name: Hephaestus
title: God of Fire and Forge
description: Hephaestus is the god of fire, metalworking, and craftsmanship. He is the blacksmith of the gods.

name: Persephone
title: Queen of the Underworld
description: Persephone is the queen of the Underworld and the goddess of spring growth. She is associated with the changing seasons.

name: Eros
title: God of Love
description: Eros is the god of love and desire. He is often depicted as a winged boy with a bow and arrow.

name: Nike
title: Goddess of Victory
description: Nike is the goddess of victory and is often depicted with wings. She represents triumph and success.
